<h2>What Is a Driver Behavior Monitoring System?</h2>
<p data-start="714" data-end="937">A Driver Behavior Monitoring System (DBMS) is a tool that collects data on how someone drives and uses it to provide insights. At GPS Company, our system uses <strong data-start="873" data-end="889">GPS tracking</strong>, sensors, and cameras to record behaviors like:</p>
<p data-start="1108" data-end="1305">This information is sent to a dashboard via our <strong data-start="1156" data-end="1193">driver behavior tracking software</strong>, where fleet managers (or business owners) can see reports, get alerts, and act when they spot risky behaviour.</p>
